content.raw: I think this expectation should be taken out because it doesn't really do anything. In 391a04c I made an integer called "matched points" and increment it every time we find a matching point between `contacts` and the contact manager contacts, and expect it to be equal to the size of `contacts` at the end of the test case (every contact found in the sim API has a match in Gazebo).
